		<item>
			<title>Lens, Aperture, &amp; Shutter</title>
			<link>https://pascoli.github.io/undergraduate-engineering/modular-camera/lens-aperture--shutter.html</link>
			<description>
				&lt;div class="article-summary"&gt;&lt;p style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 14px; font-family: Verdana;"&gt;The setup of the lens-aperture-shutter module includes two laser-cut spacers to distance our lens from the other two mechanisms but also to demonstrate the potential variability of the system when given the extra space. For example, one could build a two-element lens system and still have space to insert all of the other components into the module.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
			</description>
